1777330128920191	seal-dev	itc:v3:AWKZ8kmeSSZmc0AAAAAAQbfVb1VtuwAAAAEwJg		item.create	bn-2blj	{"description":"**File**: crates/seal-core/src/projection/mod.rs:1673-1689\n\n**Issue**: Re-applying an already-projected `CommentAdded` event leaves the comment row unchanged but still increments `threads.next_comment_number`.\n\n**Root Cause**: The comment insert is idempotent via `INSERT OR IGNORE`, but the follow-up counter update runs unconditionally and is not tied to whether a row was actually inserted.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (data integrity / correctness)\n- Scope: Any code path that replays or directly applies a duplicate `CommentAdded` event against an existing projection row\n- Reproducibility: 100% when `apply_comment_added` sees an existing `comment_id`; the comment count remains stable while `next_comment_number` advances\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\nconn.execute(\n    \"INSERT OR IGNORE INTO comments (\n        comment_id, thread_id, body, author, created_at\n    ) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\",\n    params![event.comment_id, event.thread_id, event.body, author, ts.to_rfc3339()],\n)?;\nconn.execute(\n    \"UPDATE threads SET next_comment_number = next_comment_number + 1 WHERE thread_id = ?\",\n    params![event.thread_id],\n)?;\n```\n\n**Context**: `CommentService::add_to_thread` and `CommentService::add_to_review` derive new IDs from `ProjectionDb::get_next_comment_number` (crates/seal-core/src/core/comments.rs:66-74 and 136-172). The projection tests at crates/seal-core/src/projection/mod.rs:3789-3837 assert duplicate replay does not duplicate rows, but they do not assert that `next_comment_number` remains unchanged.","kind":"bug","labels":["fresh-eyes","logic-error","data-integrity"],"size":"s","title":"Duplicate comment replay advances thread comment counters"}	blake3:bWBc9g0apZKyk6UovlQFe4f1yeUY9D5A0YoBDsR7cQU
1777330139882190	seal-dev	itc:v3:AWKZ8kmeSSZmc0AAAAAAQbfVb1VtuwAAAAEwJw		item.create	bn-xkz7	{"description":"**File**: crates/seal-cli/src/cli/commands/sarif.rs:244-315\n\n**Issue**: A single SARIF import can create duplicate threads/comments because it collects existing comments once and then keeps using the same pre-import `SealServices` projection while appending new finding events.\n\n**Root Cause**: `run_sarif_import` opens and syncs services once, stores `existing_bodies` before the loop, and never updates either `existing_bodies` or the service projection after `services.comments().add_to_review(...)` appends events.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (incorrect import results and duplicate review feedback)\n- Scope: `seal sarif import` runs containing repeated fingerprints or multiple findings at the same file/line in the same SARIF file\n- Reproducibility: 100% for duplicates within one import invocation; only findings imported before the command started participate in duplicate detection\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\nlet services = open_services(seal_root)?;\nlet existing_bodies = collect_review_comment_bodies(&services, review_id)?;\n...\nif existing_bodies.iter().any(|b| body_contains_fingerprint(b, &fingerprint)) {\n    skipped_duplicate += 1;\n    continue;\n}\n...\nlet added = services.comments().add_to_review(...)?;\nimported.push(...);\n```\n\n**Context**: The CLI advertises SARIF re-import idempotency at crates/seal-cli/src/cli/mod.rs:237-241. `CommentService::add_to_review` checks `find_thread_at_location` against the service's projection before creating a thread (crates/seal-core/src/core/comments.rs:135-168), so same-location findings added earlier in the same import are also invisible to later loop iterations.","kind":"bug","labels":["fresh-eyes","logic-error","data-integrity"],"size":"m","title":"SARIF import reuses a stale projection while adding findings"}	blake3:wKqO3Z8HKAp90zhGf_g64ZUJ8yAJ7Qt7oBr75aGMJe8
1777330150969717	seal-dev	itc:v3:AWKZ8kmeSSZmc0AAAAAAQbfVb1VtuwAAAAEwKA		item.create	bn-1642	{"description":"**File**: crates/seal-cli/src/cli/commands/comments.rs:74-85\n\n**Issue**: The `seal comment` shortcut rejects approved reviews even though the core comment service and thread creation command accept open or approved reviews.\n\n**Root Cause**: The CLI wrapper performs a stricter pre-check (`review.status != \"open\"`) before calling `CommentService::add_to_review`, while the underlying service allows both `open` and `approved` states.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (broken CLI workflow / inconsistent command behavior)\n- Scope: Users trying to add new inline feedback with `seal comment` after a review has been approved but before it is merged or abandoned\n- Reproducibility: 100% for approved reviews through the `seal comment` command\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\nif review.status != \"open\" {\n    bail!(\n        \"Cannot comment on review with status '{}': {}\",\n        review.status,\n        review_id\n    );\n}\n```\n\n**Context**: `CommentService::add_to_review` accepts `open` or `approved` at crates/seal-core/src/core/comments.rs:115-129. `seal threads create` uses the same open-or-approved policy at crates/seal-cli/src/cli/commands/threads.rs:38-44. The top-level CLI describes `seal comment` as the auto-thread path for new feedback at crates/seal-cli/src/cli/mod.rs:142.","kind":"bug","labels":["fresh-eyes","logic-error","cli"],"size":"xs","title":"seal comment rejects approved reviews despite core support"}	blake3:M78B6vCKPc3lJ4ME40RzbNGjXtNwc2LccBLiIlLq6QM
