1777332901256091	seal-dev	itc:v3:AWKZ8kmeSSZmc0AAAAAAQbfVb1VtuwAAAAEwMg		item.create	bn-1isz	{"description":"**File**: crates/seal-cli/src/cli/commands/reviews.rs:1085-1099, crates/seal-tui/src/core_client.rs:315-330, crates/seal-cli/src/cli/commands/status.rs:255-263\n\n**Issue**: Diff file extraction uses whitespace splitting on `diff --git` headers, so files whose paths contain spaces are indexed under the wrong filename.\n\n**Root Cause**: Git emits unquoted `diff --git a/src/has space.rs b/src/has space.rs` headers for paths with spaces. Splitting that line on whitespace makes the new-path token `space.rs` instead of `b/src/has space.rs`.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (incorrect diff/status/TUI review output)\n- Scope: Reviews touching files with spaces in their repository-relative paths\n- Reproducibility: 100% for ordinary Git diffs whose path includes a space; `split_whitespace().nth(3)` selects the second word of the path, not the full path\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\ncurrent_file = line\n    .split_whitespace()\n    .nth(3)\n    .map(|s| s.trim_start_matches(\"b/\"));\n```\n\n```rust\nlet parts: Vec<&str> = line.split_whitespace().collect();\nparts.get(3).map(|s| s.trim_start_matches(\"b/\").to_string())\n```\n\n**Context**: `build_file_diffs` in CLI review output and the TUI uses this map to decide which per-file diff belongs with each thread/file. `run_diff` uses the same pattern to populate `changed_files`, so output and `.sealignore` filtering can report/filter `space.rs` instead of `src/has space.rs`.","kind":"bug","labels":["fresh-eyes","logic-error","path-parsing"],"size":"m","title":"Diff header parsing breaks paths containing spaces"}	blake3:jWtb3qlmT4lSgVU7cnzMX_rtvgY5FT3qLEyYEQRybTc
1777332916703104	seal-dev	itc:v3:AWKZ8kmeSSZmc0AAAAAAQbfVb1VtuwAAAAEwMw		item.create	bn-3b6c	{"description":"**File**: crates/seal-tui/src/core_client.rs:175-195\n\n**Issue**: New TUI comments store `review.initial_commit` as the thread `commit_hash` instead of the review's current target commit.\n\n**Root Cause**: `CoreClient::comment` passes `review.initial_commit` directly into `CommentService::add_to_review`, while the CLI comment/thread paths resolve `final_commit`, `scm_anchor`, or legacy `jj_change_id` before falling back to `initial_commit`.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (incorrect anchor metadata and drift behavior)\n- Scope: TUI-created comments on reviews whose SCM anchor has advanced after review creation, or merged reviews with `final_commit`\n- Reproducibility: 100% through the TUI `comment` path whenever the current review target differs from `initial_commit`\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\nservices\n    .comments()\n    .add_to_review(\n        review_id,\n        file_path,\n        selection,\n        body,\n        review.initial_commit,\n        Some(&agent),\n    )\n```\n\n**Context**: CLI comments use `resolve_review_thread_commit` in crates/seal-cli/src/cli/commands/comments.rs:103-113, and that helper prioritizes `final_commit`, then resolved `scm_anchor`, then `jj_change_id`, then `initial_commit` at crates/seal-cli/src/cli/commands/helpers.rs:164-178. The TUI also renders diffs against the resolved target commit in `build_file_diffs` (crates/seal-tui/src/core_client.rs:227-242), so a user comments on current diff content but the stored thread points at the original review commit.","kind":"bug","labels":["fresh-eyes","logic-error","tui"],"size":"s","title":"TUI comments anchor new threads to the review's initial commit"}	blake3:rRbs7cvujNm0X5tx_a8NznRyM9lcnZfQiK6m77fF0ZQ
1777332927912647	seal-dev	itc:v3:AWKZ8kmeSSZmc0AAAAAAQbfVb1VtuwAAAAEwNA		item.create	bn-26oe	{"description":"**File**: crates/seal-tui/src/lib.rs:384-405\n\n**Issue**: When Shift+A external-editor comment submission fails to persist, the TUI silently ignores the error and gives the user no failure message.\n\n**Root Cause**: The external editor path checks only `persist_result.is_ok()` to decide whether to reload review data. Unlike the inline submission path, it never handles the `Err` branch or stores the error in `model.flash_message`.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Severity: P2 (lost user action feedback / poor error handling)\n- Scope: TUI comments submitted via the external editor path when `SealClient::comment` or `SealClient::reply` fails, such as invalid anchor metadata, stale review state, filesystem write errors, or identity errors\n- Reproducibility: 100% for persistence failures after the editor returns a non-empty body; the body is discarded from the pending request and the UI reopens without reporting the failure\n\n**Evidence**:\n```rust\nif let Ok(Some(body)) = &comment_result {\n    if let Some(client) = ctx.client.as_ref() {\n        let persist_result = persist_comment(*client, ctx.repo_path, &request, body);\n        if persist_result.is_ok() {\n            reload_review_data(model, *client, ctx.repo_path);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Context**: The inline editor path immediately below handles persistence errors and sets `model.flash_message = Some(format!(\"Comment failed: {e}\"))` at crates/seal-tui/src/lib.rs:435-449. The external path removes `pending_comment_request` before launching the editor at line 384, so a failed persistence attempt is not retried or visible to the user.","kind":"bug","labels":["fresh-eyes","error-handling","tui"],"size":"xs","title":"External TUI comment submission hides persistence failures"}	blake3:GriaBV1r-nPTaZTFtvyVsQ3EGqx4nZEF7y28sIjaDfg
